<br>
&quot; As a little girl, the call of Mithaniel Marr came to her at all moments. She could hear it louder and louder till she joined the clergi and devoted her life to the God.<br>
<br>
Her piety was strong but life at the cathedral was getting to her and when the grand priest came and seek her help in the quest to destroy the Gnolls in the evil Blackborrow, she leap with joy.<br>
<br>
She gathered her things and started her journey, meeting many on her path. Her problems with the common inglish tongue made her seek and befriend others of the french common tongue, with who she created a Guild called le&quot;Cercle des Patriotes&quot;. These friends she made and home she created were of great confort and she loved all within them dearly, till one day they turned to her for help yet again. She had no more to give them, she had done what she could and left.<br>
<br>
45 seasons had passed since she had first left the temple and every time she returned on a pilgrimage yet on this one, she felt empty, the friends she believed in and the home she had help build had crumbled. yet on this same trip, she had met a person who would help her greatly.<br>
<br>
Jaandir was older and wiser than she, and he took her into his family were he introduced her to many others. These all became her friends and tho some like Jonarky had nothing but request from the grave to be resurected, many were eager to help and gave Umberlie a taste for life once again.<br>
<br>
New lands were discovered shortly after and as the seasons passed and many adventures brought rewards. Umberlie decided she had to move on. She wanted to see more, and with a tear on her cheek and a knot in her heart, she left Jaandir and the Aequus family.<br>
<br>
She has been far and near now, seen almost all in the world. From Queynos to Feriona Vie and from the Outpost to Kael. Yet she will always remember her times in Aequus and the friendships that were forged.<br>
<br>
Umberlie<br>
56 Cleric<br>
FA<br>
