<br>
First i'll start with &quot;man what a night&quot;.  I don't know who sent out the call to get me up to PoA, probably meemers.  Anyways, i dragged 11 friends up there to hook up with the group he had in progress.  We cleared most of isle 5.  I got the toughest part of the quest for cloak of spiroc feathers.  I am still missing the disk, so will have to do another raid some time.<br>
<br>
Hit isle 6 and just got maulled by birds.  We gave up due to lack of enchanter power.   Isle 6 is a very tough break.  Very tough.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyways, that aside.  Hrm, a character bio.. <br>
<br>
Chrysalid grew up in a very harsh city.  By the time he was 14 he had fought and killed probably half of his class mates due to petty squables for power.  The Erudites of Paineel are a very unforgiving bunch.  And rising in the circles of power the necromancers control often takes much sacrifice and focus of will.  At a very early age Erudites are taught that power is everything and nothing can stand in the way of accumulating that power.  Not even death.<br>
<br>
So at 14, with half his class dead and buried behind him, Chrysalid found himself out in the world doing minor quests for his masters.  Carrying letters, assasinating minor dignitaries, and menial jobs such as fetching basic reagents.  This pleased his elders and they rewarded him with spells that enabled him to travel farther.<br>
<br>
Seeing early on that the solo life can only take a person so far, Chrysalid founded Tarot.  By helping the people in this small circle he hoped to further his dark ambition of ruling the world.  And thus Tarot grew.   As time passed however, Chrysalid decided Tarot would not progress as fast or as far as he wanted.  So he made a pact with Aequus.  He would look the other way and not slay Jaandir for his pathetic love of nature, in exchange Jaandir would admit Chrysalid's allies of Tarot into Aequus.  And thus the dark pact was forged, and one night after trashing the fool god Innoruuk's back door, Tarot swore alliegance to Aequus.  Both guilds were strengthened by the merger and life continues.<br>
<br>
These days Chrysalid likes to romp through various cities killing guards and citizens for sport.  He's been known to slay dignitaries and kings for looking at him the wrong way.  Hobbies include dropping monks to their death and embaracing other warriors by solo'ing creatures that often take a group of 6 or more to bring down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#CD7F32>- </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/baequus>Aequus</a><font color=#CD7F32> - </font><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/faequusgeneral>The Fountain</a> <font color=#CD7F32> - </font><a href="http://www.prexus.com/Aequus">Aequus</a><font color=#CD7F32> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM DEFAULT AD SCRIPT -->
